summary: ...TROPICAL STORM JERRY FORMS OVER THE TROPICAL CENTRAL ATLANTIC... ...THE TENTH NAMED STORM OF THE SEASON... As of 11:00 AM AST Tue Oct 07 the center of Jerry was located near 11.5, -44.6 with movement W at 24 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1006 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 45 mph.
